displayName.text: Vue Cinema London - West End (Leicester Square)
Church of Notre Dame de France RC
Premier Inn London Leicester Square hotel

text.text:
People say this hot pot restaurant offers a wide variety of fresh ingredients, including beef slices, crispy pork, and duck blood, and flavorful dipping sauces. They also highlight the authentic atmosphere, the friendly and helpful staff, and the delicious shaved ice desserts.

Other reviews mention the portions can be small.

originalText.text: Lovely broth and good quality ingredients — everything tasted fresh and well prepared. But despite booking in advance, we still waited more than 30 minutes to be seated, which was disappointing. The biggest downside is the price. For what we paid, the portions felt quite limited. A nice place to try once, but for the cost, I expected more generous servings and faster seating.

originalText.text: Absolutely love Nan Hotpot! The beef is super tender, the salted egg yolk shrimp balls are amazing, and the coconut ice is the perfect finish. Authentic flavors, cozy atmosphere, and great discounts — easily my favorite hotpot spot in London!

originalText.text: I recently tried Nan Hotpot, and it was absolutely amazing. The broth was rich and flavorful, perfectly balanced without being too heavy. All the ingredients were super fresh – from the tender beef slices to the crunchy vegetables – and everything tasted so satisfying when cooked in the soup. I especially loved the dipping sauces, which really elevated the flavors and made each bite unique. The atmosphere was warm and inviting, making it a great place to enjoy with friends. Definitely one of the best hotpot experiences I’ve had in a long time!

originalText.text:
I’ve tried Nan hot pot when I was in China, I have to say this hotpot is totally authentic flavor ! I do like all the fresh meat and vegetables. The meat is so tender and juicy — it just melts in my  mouth!

The soup base is really flavorful. Definitely will come again.

originalText.text:
Better than hi dialogue

If you’re looking for the ultimate hot pot experience, this place is a must-visit! The broth selection is rich and flavorful—perfectly balanced and never too salty. The ingredients are super fresh, from the thinly sliced meats to the crisp vegetables. I especially loved the dipping sauces—you can mix and match to create your own flavor, which makes it fun and personal.

The service was attentive and friendly; staff made great recommendations and kept everything topped up without us even asking. The atmosphere is cozy yet lively, making it a great spot for both casual dinners with friends and special occasions.
